Ireland's rugby union side stormed to a  64-8 victory over Western Australia in the opening clash of their Australian  tour here Wednesday night.
After the state side had stunned the visitors with an early penalty to  take the lead at the WACA Ground, Ireland fought back to be 17-3 ahead at half  time. They utterly dominated the second half.
Centre Maurice Field led the way for Ireland with three tries, while  Terence Kingston (two), Victor Costello, Jeremy Davidson, Patrick Johns and  Conor O'Shea also crossed the Western Australian line.
Flyhalf Eric Elwood converted eight of the nine tries as well as a penalty.
